name: float_f32_one
description: |
  This exact binary32 value is a baseline operand paired with both signed
  zeros. Dividing it by those inputs tests divide-by-zero handling: IEEE 754
  default arithmetic returns signed infinity, while runtimes, validators, or
  enabled traps may instead report an error. It is also paired with the next
  representable value above one to test precision-sensitive comparisons.
format: hex
decode-as: f32-le
pair:
  - with: positive-zero.input
    hint: tricky
  - with: negative-zero.input
    hint: tricky
  - with: one-plus-epsilon.input
    hint: not-equal
tags:
  - "float"
  - "floating-point"
  - "ieee-754"
  - "f32"
  - "division-by-zero"
  - "baseline"
---
00 00 80 3f   # 0x3f800000: 1
